If the original string contains [supplementary Unicode characters](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/i18n/text/supplementaryChars.html), then `split()` would not work, as it splits these characters into surrogate pairs. To correctly handle these special characters, a code like this works:

    String[] chars = new String[stringToSplit.codePointCount(0, stringToSplit.length())];
    for (int i = 0, j = 0; i &lt; stringToSplit.length(); j++) {
	    int cp = stringToSplit.codePointAt(i);
